    <name>Different Ways to Represent and Interpret ¾</name>
    <intro>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;Fractions can be represented in multiple ways—for example, as decimals or percents. To understand how these different numerical representations are related, it is helpful to see them in real-life scenarios, mathematics tasks with context, and visual diagrams.
    Multiple representations help build a robust understanding of fractions, which is key in building a strong mathematical foundation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style="padding-top: 20px;"&gt;Assignment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Show different ways of representing or interpreting the number ¾.&lt;/strong&gt; Think beyond part-to-whole relationships—consider real-life scenarios, diagrams, and contexts where the concept of ¾ might be represented in different ways. For example, in what scenario
    might learners share ¾ of a food item?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;You can submit your work in whatever medium you like (e.g., a document, a slideshow, or photos/images). Selected responses will be shared for a discussion during Session 3.3.&lt;/p&gt;
